Dagannoth Prime is the magic Dagannoth King found on Waterbirth Island. Together with Dagannoth Rex and Dagannoth Supreme, he makes up the Dagannoth Kings boss encounter. He is completely immune to magic, melee, and necromancy damage.

Dagannoth Prime is the only drop source for the Seers' ring and the mud battlestaff. Obtaining all unique drops from the Kings will unlock the Bukalla's Heir, [Name] title.

Achievements[edit | edit source]

Main article: Dagannoth Kings achievements
  • Baroo Quality ( 35) – Defeat a Dagannoth King whilst wearing full yak-hide armour and a Fremennik round shield. Can only be completed in a solo instance.
  • Dagannoth Traffic Wardens ( 40) – Defeat the Dagannoth Supreme with each different colour variation of Balmung. Can only be completed in a solo instance.
  • They All Fell Down ( 40) – Defeat the Dagannoth Kings all within 5 seconds of each other. Can only be completed in a solo instance.
  • Long Live the Kings! ( 0) – Obtained a collection of unique drops from the Dagannoth Kings.
  • Dagannoth For Everyone:
    • Dagannoth For Everyone I ( 5) – Defeat any of the Dagannoth Kings. (X/5)
    • Dagannoth For Everyone II ( 5) – Defeat any of the Dagannoth Kings. (X/10)
    • Dagannoth For Everyone III ( 5) – Defeat any of the Dagannoth Kings. (X/25)
    • Dagannoth For Everyone IV ( 5) – Defeat any of the Dagannoth Kings. (X/50)
    • Dagannoth For Everyone V ( 5) – Defeat any of the Dagannoth Kings. (X/75)
    • Dagannoth For Everyone VI ( 5) – Defeat any of the Dagannoth Kings. (X/100)

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • ninja 20 September 2022 (Update):
    • The Dagannoth King pets have been visually updated to better reflect the bosses they come from.
  • patch 11 January 2021 (Update):
    • Various bosses around RuneScape have taken their Santa Hats off for another year.
  • patch 27 January 2020 (Update):
    • Spinolyps seen in Dagannoth King fight will no longer drop items that are unreachable to the player.
  • patch 8 January 2018 (Update):
    • The aggressive monster warning from the max guild boss portal teleport to Dagannoth Kings has been removed.
  • ninja 31 July 2017 (Update):
    • A safe spot has been added to the entrance to the Dagannoth Kings.
  • patch 12 September 2016 (Update):
    • Dagannoth Kings can no longer be "walked". They will now attack players standing underneath them as intended.
  • patch 16 March 2015 (Update):
    • It is now possible to use surge in the Dagannoth Kings boss instances.
  • ninja 17 February 2014 (Update):
    • The duration of the Dagannoth King's respawn timer has been increased due to feedback from last weeks update.
  • ninja 4 February 2014 (Update):
    • Dagannoth Kings now respawn more quickly.
  • patch 3 September 2013 (Update):
    • Balmung and the Fremennik seaboots have had their boosted damage against the dagannoth kings reworked.
  • patch 25 March 2013 (Update):
    • The Dagannoth king’s attack range has been returned to the values used pre-EoC.
  • patch 6 September 2011 (Update):
    • Killing Dagannoth kings now states that the player killed a Dagannoth King (rather than Rex, Prime and Supreme) in the Adventurer's log to prevent filling the log.
  • update 7 November 2005 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Before a hidden update, when you kill Dagannoth Prime, in the Adventurer's Log it says "I killed Dagannoth Prime, one of the legendary Dagannoth Kings, rumoured to fly on the Northern Winds." Killing him after this hidden update simply says "I killed a Dagannoth King."
